\newlabel{fig:Tm_structures}{{1}{17}{$T_m$ structures for safe root existence proof. (a) In $T_1$, vertex $c$ is safe as both endpoints are neighbors. (b) In $T_2$, at least one of $c$ or $d$ is safe. (c) For $T_m$ with $m > 2$, checking vertex $a$+1 either finds it safe or reduces to smaller $T_k$}{figure.caption.2}{}}
